---
import BaseLayout from '~/layouts/BaseLayout.astro'

const updated = '2026-06-19'
---

<BaseLayout title="Disclaimer — Book Lore" description="What Book Lore is and isn't.">
  <header class="container-prose page-head">
    <p class="eyebrow"><a href="/">Book Lore</a> / <a href="/legal/">Legal</a> / Disclaimer</p>
    <h1>Disclaimer</h1>
    <p class="meta">Last updated: {updated}</p>
  </header>

  <article class="container-prose prose">
    <p>
      Everything on Book Lore is published in good faith for general information
      and education. Use it at your own risk.
    </p>

    <h2>Summaries are not substitutes</h2>
    <p>
      Book Lore entries are <em>commentary</em>: opinionated, structured notes
      that map a book. They are not the book itself. If a summary intrigues
      you, please buy the original — the author did the hard work.
    </p>

    <h2>Not financial / medical / legal advice</h2>
    <p>
      Many of the books on Book Lore touch finance, health, or law. Summaries
      and analyses are <em>about</em> what those books say; they are not
      professional advice. Consult a qualified advisor before acting.
    </p>

    <h2>External links</h2>
    <p>
      We link to third-party sites we find useful (publisher pages, OpenLibrary
      records, etc.). We don't control their content, and inclusion is not an
      endorsement.
    </p>

    <h2>Affiliate disclosure</h2>
    <p>
      Some outbound book links may, in the future, be affiliate links. This
      never affects what we summarise or analyse, and any such links will be
      marked clearly.
    </p>

    <h2>Errors</h2>
    <p>
      Spotted a factual error in a summary? Email
      <a href="mailto:whyiswhen@gmail.com">whyiswhen@gmail.com</a> or use the
      <a href="/contact/">contact form</a>. We fix typos and factual mistakes
      promptly.
    </p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .page-head { padding-block: 3rem 1.5rem; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border); }
  .eyebrow { color: var(--color-fg-muted); font-size: 0.8125rem; margin: 0 0 0.5rem; }
  .eyebrow a { color: var(--color-fg-muted); text-decoration: none; }
  h1 { font-family: var(--font-serif); font-size: clamp(2rem, 4vw, 2.75rem); font-weight: 600; letter-spacing: -0.02em; margin: 0; }
  .meta { color: var(--color-fg-soft); font-size: 0.875rem; margin: 0.5rem 0 0; }
  .prose { padding-block: 2.5rem 4rem; color: var(--color-prose); line-height: 1.7; font-size: 1.0625rem; }
  .prose h2 { font-family: var(--font-serif); font-size: 1.375rem; font-weight: 600; color: var(--color-fg); margin: 2rem 0 1rem; }
  .prose p { margin: 0 0 1.25rem; }
  .prose a { color: var(--color-accent); }
</style>
